training_examples.query: What are the requirements for a contractor license in Nevada?
training_examples.actual: California Contractors State License Board (CSLB) requirements: Class A (General Engineering) and Class B (General Building) licenses available. 4 years experience required (up to 3 years education credit, minimum 1 year practical). $25,000 bond effective 2023 (increased from $15,000). Workers compensation now mandatory for ALL contractors effective 2025 regardless of employees. Application fees: $450 application + $200-$350 license fee. This information is time-sensitive.

training_examples.query: How much does a surety bond cost?
training_examples.actual: Georgia requires contractors to be licensed for work over $2,500. General contractor license requires 4 years experience or equivalent education. Application fee is $200, with total costs ranging $300-400. Two exams required: Business & Law (110 questions, 4 hours) and Trade exam (110 questions, 4 hours). Both require 70% passing score. $10,000 surety bond required for general contractors. This information is time-sensitive.

training_examples.query: What's the ROI on getting licensed?
training_examples.expected: First project typically returns 3-10x the licensing investment
training_examples.actual: Ryan R., former superintendent, invested $3,345 in Georgia contractor license. Timeline: 35 days to license approval. Results: 150% income increase from $65K to $162K in first year. ROI: 2,735% first year return. Quote: 'I probably do about 30 projects per year now vs being assigned projects before.' Demonstrates typical income transformation for licensed contractors. This information is time-sensitive.

training_examples.query: Can I DIY the licensing process?
training_examples.actual: When customers ask about DIY licensing: 'Absolutely, many contractors try the DIY route. However, here's what our data shows: DIY success rate is only 35-45% first-time approval with 60-70% exam pass rates. That means 55-65% face delays, reapplication fees, and lost opportunities. You'll invest 80-125 hours of your time worth $6,000-$18,750. Our clients save 76-118 hours and achieve 98% approval rates. The question isn't whether you CAN do it yourself, it's whether your time is better spent building your business while we handle the paperwork.' This information is time-sensitive.

training_examples.query: What if I flunk the test?
training_examples.expected: You can retake the exam after a waiting period, additional fees apply
training_examples.actual: Texas does not require state-level general contractor licensing. Must check municipal requirements for specific cities/counties. No age, experience, or educational requirements at state level. State licensing required for specific trades: Plumbing (Responsible Master Plumber), HVAC (Class A/B with insurance requirements), Electrical (2+ years journeyman before master). Municipal bonds may be required (example: San Antonio demolition $5,000 annual bond). This information is time-sensitive.
